This paper proposes a modulation scheme for upgrading digital broadcast systems, which involves transmitting additional data in a secondary constellation while maintaining the basic constellation of the original system. This involves techniques related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.DC), as well as networking and communication protocols (cs.NI). The paper also mentions the use of satellite TV and radio, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI).
